				\begin{document}$$ESC$$\end{document}, this particularly concerns the exclusion of value added tax and other flat-rate surcharges from fuel costs in buildings. However, it was not possible to completely eliminate all relevant transfer payments in this study. To illustrate, building renovations include a significant share of labour costs that, in turn, largely consist of payroll taxes.5 A thorough elimination of all relevant transfer payments would require dedicated country- and technology-specific analyses.

